text:
I played this game since Aru and Mashiro banner started, the OSTs made my stay the game, as the game is rare with this kind of OST. Currently at level 47 and my current goal is to give T4 bags to my tanks (Tsubaki, Hoshino, Sumire). I can't finish Chesed Hardcore because my tanks are soft. So here some tips for the starters.

If you pull for waifu and not caring for meta, go for it! There's nothing wrong about that 

But if you pull for meta and fast progress, I suggest rerolling for Hibiki (1st priority) and Iori (2nd priority). Hibiki's AOE is insane that you can clear PvE easily also dangerous for PvP, Iori for 3 shot low cost long range damage that is dominating on PvE/Raids/PvP. As for the 3rd unit you want to have Haruna (PvP/PvE for blue damage), Shun (PvP), Maki (Raids), Aru and Hina (both PvE). Gura got Hoshino as her first 3*, Hoshino excels in late game - Tier 4 bag equipped and level 3 EX skill for stun. She's very disruptive on PvP but also great tank in general.

As for the 1* and 2* units, get Tsubaki as your tank as she's best tank in the game in every content. Invest also on Akari (red AoE) and Serika (red single). Akane is really good for boss fights/Raids because of her defense shred. Kotama is the only attack buffer in the game atm, investing her into 3* is also great. And lastly Serina is the best healer and unlock her 2* for extra healing.

text:
Before anyone new picks Blue Archive up, take note that its currently going through a censorship scandal. The translation team assured the playerbase before launch on multiple occasions that they had no plans to alter any of the content. Earlier this morning they went back on their word and censored a CG in the second chapter of the story. As of now, no official explanation has been given as to why. 

It's up to you to decide if that's a reason for you to skip out on playing it or not, but the combination of early broken promises, numerous players declaring their intention to leave the game,  review scores plummeting across regions and Nexon's poor track record of dropping support for games that don't live up to their expectations paints a very poor outlook for the future of Blue Archive Global.
